						               													<description>Veredicto is a fun board game, created in Argentina, where you have to defend cases and convince other players that what you say is true, in order to win!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;It's time to give your &amp;ldquo;Verdict&amp;rdquo;!!! All participants must use their ingenuity, strategy and audacity to defend a statement, whether it is true or false, and persuade the other players with arguments to win, within the dramatization of a trial where the participants will play the roles of lawyers and jury.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players must advance and add positions to win round after round each case as lawyers or by getting their verdicts right as a jury, until someone manages to win the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game is innovative and contains a large dose of entertainment because the players learn from each case and have fun watching the lawyers argue in each case. In turn, the participants test their knowledge, in a unique dynamic where everyone plays all the time.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;How to play?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The plot of the game is novel and captivating. Players take on the role of lawyers and - indicated by a card - must argue for the truth or falsity of a statement, trying to convince the other players (the &amp;quot;jury&amp;quot;) to lean towards their defense.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;It's a game for 3 to 6 players or teams where you'll be a lawyer and you'll have to defend unusual cases and convince the rest that your argument is true in order to beat your opponent. The objective of the game is to win as many cases as possible to move up in your career before the rest do. Each lawyer must defend a position regarding an affirmation, convincing the rest that what he says is correct.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
